         <div type="commentary" subtype="frontmatter" xml:space="preserve"><p>On the recto of this papyrus are the remains of three columns of a Christian letter from Rome <ref target="https://papyri.info/ddbdp/sb;6;9557">(=TM 14264, P.Amh. 1.3a)</ref>. The papyrus contains two other passages from the Bible transcribed here, as TM 62312. At the top of recto, col. 2 is a part of the first verse of the epistle to the Hebrews (P.Amh. 1.3b). The verso contains Genesis 1.1-5 in the version of the LXX and Aquila (P.Amh. 1.3c).</p></div>
         <div xml:lang="grc" type="edition" xml:space="preserve">
<div n="r" type="textpart">
<div n="Β" subtype="part" type="textpart"><ab>
